Maria Theresa, Queen of the Two Sicilies, Archduchess of Austria

Birth31 Jul 1816 - Vienna, Wien, Austrian Empire

Death8 Aug 1867 - Albano Laziale, Roma, Lazio, Kingdom of Italy

MotherPrincess,Henriette Alexandrina von Nassau-Weilburg/Henriëtte Alexandrine Frederieke Wilhelmina von Nassau-Weilburg

FatherKarl (Charles) Ludwig, Archduke Charles, Archduke of Austria

Born in Vienna, Wien, Austrian Empire on 31 Jul 1816 to Karl (Charles) Ludwig, Archduke Charles, Archduke of Austria and Princess,Henriette Alexandrina von Nassau-Weilburg/Henriëtte Alexandrine Frederieke Wilhelmina von Nassau-Weilburg. Maria Theresa, Queen of the Two Sicilies, Archduchess of Austria married Ferdinand II, King of the Two Sicilies and had 11 children. She passed away on 8 Aug 1867 in Albano Laziale, Roma, Lazio, Kingdom of Italy.

How do we create a person’s profile?
